Malaysia signs pact to make electronic purse - paper . Malaysia unveiled a plan in London on Wednesday to manufacture the world ' s first electronic purse , the New Straits Times ( NST ) newspaper reported on Thursday . The credit card - sized device is intended to act as means of storing personal data including health and finances , said the NST in a report from London . The three companies expected to jointly develop the card are Malaysia ' s T . L . Technology Research ( M ) Sdn Bhd , Britain ' s E - pass International Ltd and Iris Securities , said the NST . The announcement was made at a signing ceremony in London to drum up support for Malaysia ' s Multimedia Super Corridor , a high - technology zone south of Kuala Lumpur , said the NST . - - Kuala Lumpur newsroom ( 603 - 206 2323 ) 
